  "response": "Okay, humor is super subjective, but here are some YouTube videos that are consistently popular and often considered hilarious, broken down into categories to give you a good starting point:\n\n**Classic/Widely Loved:**\n\n*   **\"David After Dentist\":** (DavidAfterDentist) - A young boy's hilarious reaction to coming down from anesthesia after a dental visit.  It's pure, innocent, and endlessly quotable.\n*   **\"Charlie Bit My Finger\":** (HDCYT) - Another classic viral video of two young brothers, one biting the other's finger. Simple, but the younger brother's facial expressions and the older brother's reaction are comedy gold.\n*   **\"Key & Peele - Substitute Teacher\":** (Key & Peele) -  Key & Peele have a ton of great sketches, but this one, where a substitute teacher struggles with unfamiliar names, is a standout.  Brilliantly acted and written.\n*   **\"Honest Trailers\" (Screen Junkies):** (Screen Junkies) -  These trailers hilariously point out the flaws and absurdities of popular movies and TV shows.  The narrator's delivery is perfect.\n*   **\"The Mean Kitty Song\" (Talkshowboy):** (Talkshowboy) - A song about a cat who is, well, mean.  Catchy and relatable to anyone who's owned a cat with an attitude.\n\n**Sketch Comedy:**\n\n*   **\"Dry Cleaning\" (Ryan George):** (Ryan George) - Ryan George is known for his \"Pitch Meeting\" series, but this standalone sketch about the absurdity of dry cleaning is pure brilliance.\n*   **\"Every Parent at Disney\" (Studio C):** (Studio C) - Studio C has a bunch of family-friendly sketches, but this one perfectly captures the exhaustion and chaos of taking kids to Disney World.\n*   **\"Don't Hug Me I'm Scared\" (Becky and Joe):** (Becky and Joe) - Starts off seemingly as a children's show but quickly descends into surreal and dark humor.  It's disturbing and hilarious in equal measure. (Note: may not be for everyone)\n*   **\"If Google Was A Guy\" (CollegeHumor):** (CollegeHumor) - CollegeHumor was a staple of early YouTube. This series imagines what it would be like if Google was a real person.\n\n**Stand-Up/Monologue:**\n\n*   **\"Bo Burnham - 'what.' (full show)\":** (Bo Burnham) - Bo Burnham is a master of musical comedy and self-aware humor.  This entire special is fantastic.\n*    **\"Gabriel Iglesias - I'm not Fat... I'm Fluffy\":**(Gabriel Iglesias) - One of Gabriel Iglesias' most famous bits that launched his career.\n*   **\"Bill Burr - Helicopter Parents\":** (Bill Burr) - Many of Bill Burr's stand-up clips are funny, and this one about helicopter parents is a great example of his observational and slightly cynical humor.\n\n**Animation:**\n\n*   **\"Rejected\" (Don Hertzfeldt):** (Bitter Films) -  A bizarre and darkly humorous animated short about a series of increasingly strange cartoon ideas.  It's a cult classic.\n*   **\"Simon's Cat\" (Simon Tofield):** (Simon's Cat) - Simple but relatable animations about the antics of a mischievous cat.\n*   **\"Cyanide & Happiness\" (ExplosmEntertainment):** (ExplosmEntertainment) - Dark, stick-figure humor with often unexpected and absurd punchlines.\n*   **\"asdfmovie\" (TomSka):** (TomSka) - A series of extremely short, surreal, and fast-paced animated clips.\n\n**Gaming:**\n\n*   **\"SovietWomble\" (SovietWomble):** (SovietWomble) - A gaming streamer who edits his gameplay footage into highly comedic narratives.  His \"Arma 3\" and \"DayZ\" videos are particularly popular.\n*   **\"CallMeKevin\" (CallMeKevin):** (CallMeKevin) - Hilarious and chaotic gameplay, often involving intentionally breaking games.\n*   **\"OneyPlays\" (OneyNG):** (OneyNG) - A Let's Play channel with a focus on funny commentary and improvisational humor.\n\n**Things to consider when searching:**\n\n*   **Your Personal Taste:** What kind of humor do you generally enjoy? Slapstick? Observational? Dark?  Knowing this will help you narrow down your search.\n*   **Popular YouTube Channels:** Explore the channels of the creators listed above.  Most of them have a large backlog of content, so you're likely to find more videos you enjoy.\n*   **\"Try Not To Laugh\" Challenges:**  Searching for \"Try Not To Laugh\" compilations can expose you to a wide variety of funny clips.\n*   **React Channels:**  Channels that react to other videos can be a good way to discover new and funny content.\n\nHave fun exploring!  Let me know if you'd like more specific recommendations based on a certain type of humor.\n",
